WEBVTT

00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:32.210
Beyond Journey's End

00:01:29.990 --> 00:01:32.990
Episode 35: The Divine Revolte

00:01:37.850 --> 00:01:41.490
Genau's partner died
in battle the other day.

00:01:42.210 --> 00:01:47.370
So you'll be slaying demons together
on the Northern Plateau for a while.

00:01:49.410 --> 00:01:52.200
I look forward to working
with you, Mr. Genau.

00:01:54.130 --> 00:01:56.020
The Northern Plateau is as dangerous

00:01:56.020 --> 00:01:59.540
as you'd expect the farthest
reaches of the north to be.

00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:01.020
Don't hold me back.

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:06.900
Now shake hands.

00:02:20.650 --> 00:02:24.840
Methode, do you think
you are a good person?

00:02:26.420 --> 00:02:28.930
I don't understand what you're saying.

00:02:30.780 --> 00:02:33.410
My previous partner was a good person.

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:36.160
The exact opposite of me.

00:02:37.060 --> 00:02:41.370
He'd try his hardest
for complete strangers.

00:02:46.620 --> 00:02:49.310
He was always so boisterous,
so full of smiles.

00:02:50.030 --> 00:02:52.880
He treated me as casually
as an old friend,

00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:59.560
and his personality naturally
drew people to him.

00:03:06.040 --> 00:03:07.480
He was a fool.

00:03:20.500 --> 00:03:22.910
He died protecting a child.

00:03:25.490 --> 00:03:28.260
Because of that,
we failed to kill the demon.

00:03:30.670 --> 00:03:34.210
I'd never do anything so stupid.

00:03:36.650 --> 00:03:38.890
I've forsaken countless people already.

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:42.650
Why me?

00:03:44.050 --> 00:03:45.170
What do you mean?

00:03:45.500 --> 00:03:47.730
Why was I chosen to work with you?

00:03:48.770 --> 00:03:52.500
Who knows? It was Ms. Serie's decision.

00:03:55.820 --> 00:04:01.690
All I can say is that first-class mages
who get dispatched to the Northern Plateau

00:04:02.300 --> 00:04:05.620
are usually the type that loves fighting
more than three meals a day.

00:04:08.090 --> 00:04:09.900
It certainly is strange.

00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:13.610
Why you, and not Übel?

00:04:15.200 --> 00:04:19.780
Either way, no decent
person likes fighting.

00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:24.030
Don't end up like me.

00:04:30.690 --> 00:04:35.560
Let's share what information we have
before we begin our search.

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:36.440
Very well.

00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:40.400
Based on traces of magic
and other evidence,

00:04:40.400 --> 00:04:43.680
there are four primary demons
who attacked the village.

00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:46.430
All four have vanished from the area.

00:04:46.430 --> 00:04:48.360
Four? That's a lot.

00:04:49.870 --> 00:04:52.740
One of them was a demon general.

00:04:52.740 --> 00:04:55.910
It killed the knights with four swords.

00:05:00.230 --> 00:05:02.460
What exactly is a demon general?

00:05:02.460 --> 00:05:05.510
A highly skilled and experienced
demon warrior.

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:09.910
They fight by enhancing their physical
capabilities with powerful magic.

00:05:10.390 --> 00:05:15.790
Some are devotees who spend hundreds
of years perfecting their martial skills.

00:05:16.180 --> 00:05:20.040
Some of the generals in the Demon King's
army were far stronger than Eisen.

00:05:20.330 --> 00:05:21.830
Seriously?

00:05:21.830 --> 00:05:27.580
Also, it's likely that it has
a far-from-human appearance.

00:05:27.580 --> 00:05:30.050
Is that bad?

00:05:30.730 --> 00:05:35.430
Have you ever fought an expert swordsman
who wields four swords at once?

00:05:35.890 --> 00:05:37.550
Of course not.

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:39.180
Me neither.

00:05:39.580 --> 00:05:42.420
That's probably why the knights lost.

00:05:49.810 --> 00:05:51.480
Lord Revolte.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:55.510
Our prey has been caught in our net.

00:05:55.510 --> 00:05:57.710
They're a tasty meal, rich in mana.

00:05:58.040 --> 00:06:00.580
One warrior, three mages.

00:06:00.580 --> 00:06:02.650
Three are first-class.

00:06:04.450 --> 00:06:07.310
We can handle that many.

00:06:07.310 --> 00:06:08.790
Shall we attack?

00:06:09.340 --> 00:06:10.600
No.

00:06:11.310 --> 00:06:13.620
I have a bad feeling about them.

00:06:13.620 --> 00:06:15.970
We'll wait for them to split up.

00:06:15.970 --> 00:06:22.510
Do you think they will, Lord Revolte?
They seemed rather guarded.

00:06:23.460 --> 00:06:25.600
They will.

00:06:30.470 --> 00:06:34.290
That's why we provoked them
by killing all those people.

00:06:35.740 --> 00:06:41.280
In the course of destroying all these
villages on the Northern Plateau,

00:06:41.280 --> 00:06:43.420
I've noticed something.

00:06:43.420 --> 00:06:45.410
Ooh, what is it?

00:06:49.310 --> 00:06:52.730
Let's go look for the demons.

00:06:53.360 --> 00:06:56.720
We'll head to the abandoned fort
to the north first.

00:06:57.260 --> 00:07:01.710
Demons often hide out
in places like that.

00:07:04.120 --> 00:07:05.060
Wait.

00:07:06.540 --> 00:07:09.270
The Chivalric Order of Norm
still needs to collect the bodies.

00:07:09.270 --> 00:07:11.460
Someone should stay
in the village until then.

00:07:13.640 --> 00:07:15.020
I'll remain behind.

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:20.460
Humans have a habit of remaining
in villages to protect their corpses.

00:07:21.640 --> 00:07:24.710
How interesting. Why do they do that?

00:07:25.240 --> 00:07:27.710
We don't need to know the reason.

00:07:27.710 --> 00:07:32.380
I wonder why, though.
I'm so very, very curious.

00:07:32.840 --> 00:07:37.840
You're interested in humans?
You're a strange one.

00:07:38.480 --> 00:07:43.220
Humans sometimes behave
illogically and irrationally.

00:07:43.220 --> 00:07:45.860
I want to know why they do that.

00:07:46.160 --> 00:07:49.950
That's just how they are.
There's nothing more to it.

00:07:49.950 --> 00:07:52.180
We don't need to know why.

00:07:54.500 --> 00:08:01.510
Come to think of it, I've heard of an
eccentric demon who studies humanity.

00:08:01.800 --> 00:08:06.380
Really? Tell me more about them, please!

00:08:06.950 --> 00:08:09.880
If you think it will be
of use to you, I will.

00:08:10.470 --> 00:08:14.850
You will? Then it's a promise,
Lord Revolte!

00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:18.390
You'll stay by yourself?

00:08:18.390 --> 00:08:21.400
They shouldn't be much longer.

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:26.150
I'll meet up with you once the
Order has collected the bodies.

00:08:26.820 --> 00:08:27.990
Fine.

00:08:35.180 --> 00:08:36.950
I'll stay, too.

00:08:37.590 --> 00:08:39.410
Are you stupid?

00:08:39.830 --> 00:08:42.660
Your party is heading out to fight demons.

00:08:42.660 --> 00:08:44.670
What will they do without a front-liner?

00:08:44.670 --> 00:08:46.910
The same goes for you.

00:08:46.910 --> 00:08:49.420
What if the demons return to the village?

00:08:49.690 --> 00:08:51.060
It won't be a problem.

00:08:51.060 --> 00:08:54.570
I can fight well enough
without a front-liner.

00:08:54.570 --> 00:08:57.440
So can Frieren and the others.

00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.340
There's only so much
we can handle, though.

00:08:59.340 --> 00:09:02.680
But if things look bad,
you can run, right?

00:09:02.680 --> 00:09:03.800
I guess so.

00:09:04.360 --> 00:09:07.510
You can't run away, though.
You'd be abandoning the village.

00:09:10.210 --> 00:09:13.780
Stark. All that's left here is the dead.

00:09:14.100 --> 00:09:17.280
And that's who you're staying
to protect, right?

00:09:20.230 --> 00:09:21.580
Suit yourself.

00:09:36.340 --> 00:09:39.340
Stark, you're a good person.

00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:43.720
I've known people like you.

00:09:43.720 --> 00:09:45.560
They tend not to live long.

00:09:47.960 --> 00:09:51.340
You seem like a good person to me, too.

00:09:54.140 --> 00:09:57.570
You're still trying to defend the village,
even after it's been destroyed.

00:09:58.910 --> 00:10:00.840
I couldn't do that.

00:10:07.330 --> 00:10:09.690
I'm not a good person.

00:10:10.250 --> 00:10:12.660
Quite the opposite.

00:10:14.120 --> 00:10:18.170
I've done whatever it took to
bring peace to the northern lands.

00:10:18.880 --> 00:10:23.450
I've killed and forsaken many people.

00:10:24.770 --> 00:10:26.800
Perhaps this is what I deserve.

00:10:27.350 --> 00:10:29.870
You get used to people dying, you know.

00:10:32.910 --> 00:10:35.050
I don't feel even slightly sad.

00:10:35.660 --> 00:10:38.620
My hometown's been destroyed,
but I feel nothing.

00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:44.690
I'm only staying in this village
because I thought I should.

00:10:46.510 --> 00:10:48.990
I've forsaken so many in the past,

00:10:49.850 --> 00:10:52.900
so what am I even doing?

00:10:57.920 --> 00:11:03.710
Stark, many people call
the Northern Plateau home.

00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:17.620
From now on, avoid using
long-range detection.

00:11:18.180 --> 00:11:20.820
If they're skilled, they
can trace it back to us.

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:21.780
Okay.

00:11:22.160 --> 00:11:26.510
That said, we still have a ways
to go before we reach the fort.

00:11:26.510 --> 00:11:28.530
Let's talk while we walk.

00:11:29.570 --> 00:11:31.390
Should we be doing that?

00:11:31.390 --> 00:11:34.200
It's important to ease the tension.

00:11:36.980 --> 00:11:38.590
She looks so careless.

00:11:41.670 --> 00:11:45.580
Also, communication improves teamwork.

00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:47.410
I bet you didn't know that.

00:11:47.410 --> 00:11:48.490
I see.

00:11:49.180 --> 00:11:53.540
In that case, Ms. Frieren, may I pet you?

00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:56.290
Is she actually saying that
with a straight face?

00:11:56.290 --> 00:12:01.320
I love giving headpats to small girls,

00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:04.730
but Ms. Serie doesn't let me do it often.

00:12:05.450 --> 00:12:09.170
Not only that, but she always
looks so displeased when I do.

00:12:09.170 --> 00:12:11.530
I would, too.

00:12:12.480 --> 00:12:16.360
And besides, I'm the older
one here by far, Methode.

00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:18.430
I won't suffer headpats
from the likes of you.

00:12:18.430 --> 00:12:21.620
That's right. Ms. Frieren
is a mature lady.

00:12:21.620 --> 00:12:23.590
Don't think you can casually touch her.

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:26.410
Ms. Frieren.

00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:30.100
This contains a spell

00:12:30.100 --> 00:12:34.370
that prevents pieces of shell from
falling in when cracking eggs.

00:12:35.500 --> 00:12:37.380
You can pet me all you want.

00:12:37.380 --> 00:12:38.740
Ms. Frieren?

00:12:45.830 --> 00:12:49.430
I can't believe you're allowing me
to pet you this much.

00:12:49.990 --> 00:12:52.730
No more than ten minutes per day.

00:12:52.730 --> 00:12:53.860
But...

00:13:01.890 --> 00:13:07.010
Ms. Frieren, may I hug you a little?

00:13:07.010 --> 00:13:09.670
Ms. Serie never let me.

00:13:10.140 --> 00:13:11.830
You can do whatever you want.

00:13:11.830 --> 00:13:13.430
Whatever I want?!

00:13:22.290 --> 00:13:24.260
Huh? What?

00:13:26.590 --> 00:13:29.450
Hey, stop.

00:13:30.920 --> 00:13:33.950
You'll tear me in half...

00:13:38.930 --> 00:13:40.000
Is this...?

00:13:40.580 --> 00:13:45.200
We've been detected.
They know where we are.

00:13:45.800 --> 00:13:47.280
That's demons for you.

00:13:47.960 --> 00:13:50.020
They're aggressive.

00:13:50.540 --> 00:13:55.760
They must know we're skilled mages,
but that doesn't faze them.

00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:00.650
They noticed.

00:14:01.440 --> 00:14:03.830
I see. Shall we begin?

00:14:07.430 --> 00:14:08.930
Nebeladora.

00:14:14.630 --> 00:14:16.660
It's a fog made of mana.

00:14:16.660 --> 00:14:19.270
They're blocking our vision
and mana detection.

00:14:33.300 --> 00:14:35.650
We've been separated from Methode.

00:14:36.210 --> 00:14:37.510
They're skilled.

00:14:42.060 --> 00:14:43.390
Which one do you want?

00:14:43.390 --> 00:14:47.840
The tall one has an
unusual aura about her.

00:14:47.840 --> 00:14:49.830
She should be fun.

00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:53.700
Then I'll take the other two.

00:14:56.530 --> 00:14:59.170
Watch out for attacks from above.

00:14:59.570 --> 00:15:00.660
Ms. Frieren.

00:15:01.240 --> 00:15:02.300
What?

00:15:02.800 --> 00:15:05.060
Both demons were flying.

00:15:05.770 --> 00:15:08.260
So were the demons we fought before.

00:15:08.720 --> 00:15:10.810
That's flying magic, isn't it?

00:15:11.220 --> 00:15:12.930
I told you.

00:15:13.270 --> 00:15:17.440
Until forty years ago,
demons ruled the skies.

00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:20.170
They haven't lost those skills.

00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:24.820
But you said demons only
study one type of magic.

00:15:25.780 --> 00:15:29.390
Do you think of walking
as a special ability?

00:15:30.520 --> 00:15:32.250
It's the same principle.

00:15:32.670 --> 00:15:36.580
To demons, flying magic isn't even magic.

00:15:37.180 --> 00:15:40.500
That's why this is a common sight
when fighting them.

00:15:42.910 --> 00:15:45.830
As I thought, they're
accustomed to battle.

00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:49.380
They fight like members
of the Demon King's army.

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:03.470
Methode has engaged the enemy.

00:16:03.730 --> 00:16:06.690
Fern, you'll handle the fighting.

00:16:06.690 --> 00:16:08.220
Why?

00:16:08.480 --> 00:16:11.680
This job was assigned
to the first-class mages.

00:16:12.180 --> 00:16:14.660
You're the first-class mage here.

00:16:15.340 --> 00:16:17.610
Ms. Frieren, is now
really the time for that?

00:16:18.090 --> 00:16:21.730
It won't be a problem. You can beat him.

00:16:30.310 --> 00:16:31.430
See?

00:16:32.230 --> 00:16:33.300
Oh?

00:16:35.130 --> 00:16:36.860
That was just a fluke.

00:16:38.030 --> 00:16:41.270
I only reacted in time
because you pointed.

00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:45.000
I couldn't detect his attack at all.

00:16:49.890 --> 00:16:52.000
He's better than me.

00:16:52.000 --> 00:16:53.990
I disagree.

00:16:54.880 --> 00:16:59.340
Not many first-class mages are as
dedicated to the fundamentals as you.

00:17:01.040 --> 00:17:04.280
It's all right. You can beat him.

00:17:14.740 --> 00:17:18.350
I caught some fish.
How about a late-night snack?

00:17:19.110 --> 00:17:22.860
I'll pass. Methode will be angry with me.

00:17:22.860 --> 00:17:25.380
She says it's unhealthy
to eat late at night.

00:17:25.380 --> 00:17:27.970
Oh, yeah? More for me, then.

00:17:32.110 --> 00:17:35.060
I always get hungry at this hour.

00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:41.660
Don't tell Fern.

00:17:41.660 --> 00:17:42.570
Sure.

00:17:47.260 --> 00:17:49.730
You seem to be dealing with a lot, too.

00:17:55.540 --> 00:17:57.010
Hey, Genau.

00:17:58.060 --> 00:18:01.700
You know the demon who attacked
this village, don't you?

00:18:01.700 --> 00:18:05.500
Demons that fight with four
swords are hardly common.

00:18:07.480 --> 00:18:12.370
The Divine Revolte is the
demon who killed my partner.

00:18:15.130 --> 00:18:17.730
That's a grandiose name.

00:18:18.400 --> 00:18:22.980
It comes from the four swords
he created using magic.

00:18:23.900 --> 00:18:27.670
He can freely change
the weight of his swords.

00:18:28.120 --> 00:18:31.460
Sometimes they're sharp
and light as a feather.

00:18:31.460 --> 00:18:33.830
Sometimes they're as heavy as a boulder.

00:18:35.160 --> 00:18:38.690
They're called the Divine Cleaving Swords,

00:18:38.690 --> 00:18:41.360
after the blade that split mountains
during mythical times.

00:18:41.870 --> 00:18:46.330
So they're both light and sharp
and unbelievably heavy.

00:18:47.170 --> 00:18:49.100
It's contradictory, isn't it?

00:18:50.260 --> 00:18:54.030
Magic can create objects
that shouldn't exist.

00:18:54.970 --> 00:18:59.320
In particular, weapons made from magic
are the embodiment of murderous intent.

00:19:00.230 --> 00:19:03.680
Demons that create such
weapons kill many people—

00:19:04.730 --> 00:19:09.520
far more than necessary,
as if to test them.

00:19:15.070 --> 00:19:15.790
Stark.

00:19:16.990 --> 00:19:19.540
I know. It's the enemy.

00:19:23.420 --> 00:19:24.760
It's fast.

00:19:25.650 --> 00:19:26.550
Here it comes.

00:19:57.990 --> 00:19:59.630
Four swords!

00:20:01.220 --> 00:20:04.800
One warrior and one first-class mage.

00:20:05.240 --> 00:20:09.450
As I predicted,
you're protecting the village.

00:20:10.320 --> 00:20:11.920
That's Revolte.

00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:13.640
This is him?

00:20:13.900 --> 00:20:16.500
You seem to know who I am.

00:20:17.620 --> 00:20:21.930
That first-class mage
in particular looks familiar.

00:20:22.820 --> 00:20:24.140
Who are you?

00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:27.010
Let's begin, Stark.

00:20:27.010 --> 00:20:29.920
Avoid taking his attacks head-on.

00:20:29.920 --> 00:20:32.980
Worst case, it could destroy you.

00:20:34.390 --> 00:20:36.780
I said, who are you?

00:20:37.010 --> 00:20:42.290
Do you declare your name
before exterminating a pest?

00:20:42.800 --> 00:20:45.910
You're one twisted person.

00:20:47.430 --> 00:20:50.810
We're both capable of speech, are we not?

00:20:51.830 --> 00:20:56.520
But if you don't wish to talk...

00:20:59.460 --> 00:21:03.330
then I, too, shall focus on
exterminating the pests before me.

00:21:05.170 --> 00:21:08.530
What am I supposed to do
if I can't take his attacks head-on?

00:21:08.530 --> 00:21:11.390
A warrior can deflect blows, can he not?

00:21:15.940 --> 00:21:17.400
Yeah, but...

00:21:28.660 --> 00:21:30.460
I can't protect you like that!

00:21:30.870 --> 00:21:33.140
I don't need protecting.

00:21:33.530 --> 00:21:36.770
Despite how I may seem,
I'm skilled in close-quarters combat.

00:21:57.000 --> 00:22:03.450
Demon magic isn't the only magic capable
of producing objects that shouldn't exist.

00:22:04.460 --> 00:22:06.410
Digardnacht.

00:22:11.120 --> 00:22:14.410
A spell to manipulate niello wings.

00:22:16.570 --> 00:22:18.060
Interesting.

00:22:20.980 --> 00:22:25.110
Translation
Sho Stifler
Editing & Typesetting
Geoff Mazzolini
Subtitle Timing
Edgar Cruz
Quality Check
Alicia Ashby
Translation Check
Elizabeth Ellis

00:23:50.150 --> 00:23:54.080
It's nice to watch from afar
once in a while.

00:23:50.630 --> 00:23:51.920
It's a bad matchup.

00:23:51.920 --> 00:23:53.550
She simply has no openings.

00:23:52.470 --> 00:23:53.850
I can't read his attacks.

00:23:53.850 --> 00:23:54.350
I did it!

00:23:54.350 --> 00:23:56.470
This should be a good match.

00:23:54.660 --> 00:23:57.370
It's pointless trying
to conceal your mana and hide.

00:23:56.460 --> 00:23:58.190
I shall put you out of your misery.

00:23:57.990 --> 00:24:00.070
Episode 36
A Magnificent End

00:23:58.190 --> 00:24:00.100
He met a magnificent end.

00:24:01.305 --> 00:25:01.492
